Four disks is best. One each for logs, scratch, state, and warcs.

On Wed, April 11, 2012 12:10 pm, Bjarne Andersen wrote:
&gt;  If possible try to have your logs directory setup to be on another disk than
&gt; your arcs (or warcs) directory. I guess this Will improve performance and
&gt; avoid some disk head movement
