&gt;
&gt; Hi all,
&gt;
&gt; We are two students of the University of Padova, Italy. We are attempting a
&gt; large crawl using the Heritrix crawler (version 1.14.4). The frontier we are
&gt; using is the bdbfrontier. We noticed that using this frontier, the crawler is
&gt; constantly accessing the disk, performing small reads/writes that
&gt; a) are inefficient in terms of aggregated disk I/O
&gt; b) move the disk head a lot, which is not very healthy for the disk itself. In
&gt; fact, we have already lost multiple disks in the process.
&gt;
&gt; Is there some way to avoid this problem?
&gt;
&gt; Thanks for the help
&gt;
&gt; Matteo Ceccarello,
